  "body": "The usage for [`bind-address`](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/cmd/kube-apiserver/app/server.go#L186), a flag for `apiserver`, is kinda odd. \n\nThere is no flag `--read-only-port` for `apiserver` to my best knowledge(instead, it's a flag for `kubelet`), which is referenced here.\n\nHopefully it's a typo. \n\n```\nfs.IPVar(&s.BindAddress, \"bind-address\", s.BindAddress, \"\"+\n        \"The IP address on which to serve the --read-only-port and --secure-port ports. The \"+\n        \"associated interface(s) must be reachable by the rest of the cluster, and by CLI/web \"+\n        \"clients. If blank, all interfaces will be used (0.0.0.0).\")\n```\n",
